[
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Therefore what advantage does the Jew have, or what is the value of circumcision? "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Actually, there are many advantages."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " First of all,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the Jews"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " were entrusted with the oracles of God."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " What then? If some did not believe, does their unbelief nullify the faithfulness of God? "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Absolutely not! Let God be proven true, and every human being"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " shown up as a liar,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " just as it is written: “"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "so that you will be justified"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": " in your words and will prevail when you are judged"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ".”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But if our unrighteousness demonstrates"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the righteousness of God, what shall we say? The God who inflicts wrath is not unrighteous, is he?"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " (I am speaking in human terms.)"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Absolutely not! For otherwise how could God judge the world? "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For if by my lie the truth of God enhances"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " his glory, why am I still actually being judged as a sinner? "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " And why not say, “Let us do evil so that good may come of it”? – as some who slander us allege that we say."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " (Their"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " condemnation is deserved!)"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " What then? Are we better off? Certainly not, for we have already charged that Jews and Greeks alike are all under sin, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " just as it is written: "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "“"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "There is no one righteous"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "not even one"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "there is no one who understands"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ","
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "there is no one who seeks God"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ". "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "All have turned away"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "together they have become worthless; "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "there is no one who shows kindness"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "not even one."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "Their throats are open graves"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ","
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "they deceive with their tongues"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ","
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "the poison of asps is under their lips"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "Their mouths are"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "full of cursing and bitterness"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "Their feet are swift to shed blood"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ","
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "ruin and misery are in their paths"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ","
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "and the way of peace they have not known"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "There is no fear of God before their eyes"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now we know that whatever the law says, it says to those who are under"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the law, so that every mouth may be silenced and the whole world may be held accountable to God. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "no one is declared righteous before him"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " by the works of the law,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " for through the law comes"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the knowledge of sin. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But now"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " apart from the law the righteousness of God (which is attested by the law and the prophets)"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " has been disclosed – "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " namely, the righteousness of God through the faithfulness of Jesus Christ"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " for all who believe. For there is no distinction, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " for all have sinned and fall short of the glory of God. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But they are justified"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " freely by his grace through the redemption that is in Christ Jesus. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " God publicly displayed"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " him"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " at his death"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " as the mercy seat"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " accessible through faith."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " This was to demonstrate"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " his righteousness, because God in his forbearance had passed over the sins previously committed."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " This was"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " also to demonstrate"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " his righteousness in the present time, so that he would be just"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and the justifier of the one who lives because of Jesus’ faithfulness."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Where, then, is boasting?"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " It is excluded! By what principle?"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Of works? No, but by the principle of faith! "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For we consider that a person"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " is declared righteous by faith apart from the works of the law."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Or is God the God of the Jews only? Is he not the God of the Gentiles too? Yes, of the Gentiles too! "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Since God is one,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " he will justify the circumcised by faith and the uncircumcised through faith. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Do we then nullify"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the law through faith? Absolutely not! Instead"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " we uphold the law."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  }
]